Prerequisites:
Kubernetes server installed and configured .
create external directories , so podes will access them after creation :

for mysql database: 
/mnt/data/mysql1  
/mnt/data/mysql2  
/mnt/data/mysql3

for ubuntu scripts:
/mnt/data0
copy all files from  scripts_for_ubuntu to that directory 

for NodeJS scripts:
/mnt/data1
copy all files from scripts_for_NodeJS to that directory


STEP 1:   -----create MySQL server serction-----
choose the correct directory 
for 1 replicatiion use stateful-mysql-only-1-replica-ok directory :
# kubectl apply  -f mysql-configmap.yaml  
# kubectl apply  -f mysql-services.yaml  
# kubectl apply  -f mysql-statefulset.yaml 
 
for 3 replications ( 1 read-write and 2 read-only) choose  stateful-mysql-3-replica-ok directory:
# kubectl apply -f mysql-configmap.yaml
# kubectl apply  -f mysql-pv.yaml  
# kubectl apply  -f mysql-services.yaml  
# kubectl apply  -f mysql-statefulset.yaml

STEP 2: ----create ubuntu server with python scripts-----
use the "ubuntu" directory , run all yaml files 
# kubectl apply -f pv-claim.yaml  
# kubectl apply -f pv-volume.yaml  
# kubectl apply -f ubuntu.yaml

STEP 3: ---create NodeJS server-----
use the "nodejs" directory , run all yaml files 
# kubectl apply -f pv-claim1.yaml  
# kubectl apply -f pv-volume1.yaml
# kubectl apply -f nodejs.yaml  


STEP 4: -----check --------------
connect to ubuntu pod that was created, all external scripts are located at  /external  ( mounted to /data/mnt0 of the host), try to run the scripts
connect to nodejs pod that was created, all external scripts are located at  /external  ( mounted to /data/mnt1 of the host), try to run the scripts
